# ============================================================
# QUEST CORE ARCHITECTURE
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: architecture
domain: quest
scope: quest.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of quest in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Quest is the bounded objective structure
through which declared goals,
conditions,
progress,
branching,
completion,
and failure
become meaningful.

Quest is not merely a task line.
It is the governed goal-progress unit
that binds objective meaning to stateful progression.

## architectural_position
Quest sits between:
- actor activity
- event-triggered progression
- item/inventory dependencies
- world/nation/location context
- reward or closure consequences

## required_behavior
- quest identity must remain explicit
- objective basis must remain explicit
- progress state must remain explicit
- completion and failure must remain distinguishable
- historical quest trace must remain preserved

## canonical_rules
- quest proposal does not imply active quest
- completion must not overwrite failure history
- branching must remain reviewable
- historical quest state must remain queryable
- ambiguous quest progression fails closed

## state_model
The quest domain distinguishes:
- proposed quest
- active quest
- blocked quest
- branching quest
- completed quest
- failed quest
- historical quest

## actor_boundary
- quest holder
- quest issuer
- reviewer
- operator
- adapter

## decision_matrix
- if objective basis is missing, stop activation
- if progress basis is unclear, fail closed
- if completion conditions are unmet, deny closure
- if branching occurs, preserve route trace
- if quest becomes historical, preserve result trace

## review_checklist
- objective basis is explicit
- progress model is explicit
- completion/failure distinction is explicit
- historical distinction is explicit
